#: ../../../intro/install.rst:5
msgid "Installation guide"
msgstr "安裝指南"

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:10
msgid "Supported Python versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:12
msgid ""
"Scrapy requires Python 3.10+, either the CPython implementation (default) or "
"the PyPy implementation (see :ref:`python:implementations`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:18
msgid "Installing Scrapy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:20
msgid ""
"If you're using `Anaconda`_ or `Miniconda`_, you can install the package "
"from the `conda-forge`_ channel, which has up-to-date packages for Linux, "
"Windows and macOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:24
msgid "To install Scrapy using ``conda``, run::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:26 ../../../intro/install.rst:109
msgid "conda install -c conda-forge scrapy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:28
msgid ""
"Alternatively, if you’re already familiar with installation of Python "
"packages, you can install Scrapy and its dependencies from PyPI with::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:31 ../../../intro/install.rst:211
msgid "pip install Scrapy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:33
msgid ""
"We strongly recommend that you install Scrapy in :ref:`a dedicated "
"virtualenv <intro-using-virtualenv>`, to avoid conflicting with your system "
"packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:36
msgid ""
"Note that sometimes this may require solving compilation issues for some "
"Scrapy dependencies depending on your operating system, so be sure to check "
"the :ref:`intro-install-platform-notes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:40
msgid ""
"For more detailed and platform-specific instructions, as well as "
"troubleshooting information, read on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:45
msgid "Things that are good to know"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:47
msgid ""
"Scrapy is written in pure Python and depends on a few key Python packages "
"(among others):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:49
msgid "`lxml`_, an efficient XML and HTML parser"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:50
msgid "`parsel`_, an HTML/XML data extraction library written on top of lxml,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:51
msgid ""
"`w3lib`_, a multi-purpose helper for dealing with URLs and web page encodings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:52
msgid "`twisted`_, an asynchronous networking framework"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:53
msgid ""
"`cryptography`_ and `pyOpenSSL`_, to deal with various network-level "
"security needs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:55
msgid ""
"Some of these packages themselves depend on non-Python packages that might "
"require additional installation steps depending on your platform. Please "
"check :ref:`platform-specific guides below <intro-install-platform-notes>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:59
msgid ""
"In case of any trouble related to these dependencies, please refer to their "
"respective installation instructions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:62
msgid "`lxml installation`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:63
msgid ":doc:`cryptography installation <cryptography:installation>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:71
msgid "Using a virtual environment (recommended)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:73
msgid ""
"TL;DR: We recommend installing Scrapy inside a virtual environment on all "
"platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:76
msgid ""
"Python packages can be installed either globally (a.k.a system wide), or in "
"user-space. We do not recommend installing Scrapy system wide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:79
msgid ""
"Instead, we recommend that you install Scrapy within a so-called \"virtual "
"environment\" (:mod:`venv`). Virtual environments allow you to not conflict "
"with already-installed Python system packages (which could break some of "
"your system tools and scripts), and still install packages normally with "
"``pip`` (without ``sudo`` and the likes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:85
msgid "See :ref:`tut-venv` on how to create your virtual environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:87
msgid ""
"Once you have created a virtual environment, you can install Scrapy inside "
"it with ``pip``, just like any other Python package. (See :ref:`platform-"
"specific guides <intro-install-platform-notes>` below for non-Python "
"dependencies that you may need to install beforehand)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:96
msgid "Platform specific installation notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:101
msgid "Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:103
msgid ""
"Though it's possible to install Scrapy on Windows using pip, we recommend "
"you install `Anaconda`_ or `Miniconda`_ and use the package from the `conda-"
"forge`_ channel, which will avoid most installation issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:107
msgid ""
"Once you've installed `Anaconda`_ or `Miniconda`_, install Scrapy with::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:111
msgid "To install Scrapy on Windows using ``pip``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:114
msgid ""
"This installation method requires “Microsoft Visual C++” for installing some "
"Scrapy dependencies, which demands significantly more disk space than "
"Anaconda."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:117
msgid ""
"Download and execute `Microsoft C++ Build Tools`_ to install the Visual "
"Studio Installer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:119
msgid "Run the Visual Studio Installer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:121
msgid "Under the Workloads section, select **C++ build tools**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:123
msgid ""
"Check the installation details and make sure following packages are selected "
"as optional components:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:125
msgid "**MSVC**  (e.g MSVC v142 - VS 2019 C++ x64/x86 build tools (v14.23) )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:127
msgid "**Windows SDK**  (e.g Windows 10 SDK (10.0.18362.0))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:129
msgid "Install the Visual Studio Build Tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:131
msgid ""
"Now, you should be able to :ref:`install Scrapy <intro-install-scrapy>` "
"using ``pip``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:136
msgid "Ubuntu 14.04 or above"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:138
msgid ""
"Scrapy is currently tested with recent-enough versions of lxml, twisted and "
"pyOpenSSL, and is compatible with recent Ubuntu distributions. But it should "
"support older versions of Ubuntu too, like Ubuntu 14.04, albeit with "
"potential issues with TLS connections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:143
msgid ""
"**Don't** use the ``python-scrapy`` package provided by Ubuntu, they are "
"typically too old and slow to catch up with the latest Scrapy release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:147
msgid ""
"To install Scrapy on Ubuntu (or Ubuntu-based) systems, you need to install "
"these dependencies::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:150
msgid ""
"sudo apt-get install python3 python3-dev python3-pip libxml2-dev libxslt1-"
"dev zlib1g-dev libffi-dev libssl-dev"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:152
msgid ""
"``python3-dev``, ``zlib1g-dev``, ``libxml2-dev`` and ``libxslt1-dev`` are "
"required for ``lxml``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:154
msgid "``libssl-dev`` and ``libffi-dev`` are required for ``cryptography``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:156
msgid ""
"Inside a :ref:`virtualenv <intro-using-virtualenv>`, you can install Scrapy "
"with ``pip`` after that::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:159
msgid "pip install scrapy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:162
msgid ""
"The same non-Python dependencies can be used to install Scrapy in Debian "
"Jessie (8.0) and above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:169
msgid "macOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:171
msgid ""
"Building Scrapy's dependencies requires the presence of a C compiler and "
"development headers. On macOS this is typically provided by Apple’s Xcode "
"development tools. To install the Xcode command-line tools, open a terminal "
"window and run::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:176
msgid "xcode-select --install"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:178
msgid ""
"There's a `known issue <https://github.com/pypa/pip/issues/2468>`_ that "
"prevents ``pip`` from updating system packages. This has to be addressed to "
"successfully install Scrapy and its dependencies. Here are some proposed "
"solutions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:183
msgid ""
"*(Recommended)* **Don't** use system Python. Install a new, updated version "
"that doesn't conflict with the rest of your system. Here's how to do it "
"using the `homebrew`_ package manager:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:187
msgid "Install `homebrew`_ following the instructions in https://brew.sh/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:189
msgid ""
"Update your ``PATH`` variable to state that homebrew packages should be used "
"before system packages (Change ``.bashrc`` to ``.zshrc`` accordingly if "
"you're using `zsh`_ as default shell)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:193
msgid "echo \"export PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:$PATH\" >> ~/.bashrc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:195
msgid "Reload ``.bashrc`` to ensure the changes have taken place::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:197
msgid "source ~/.bashrc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:199
msgid "Install python::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:201
msgid "brew install python"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:203
msgid ""
"*(Optional)* :ref:`Install Scrapy inside a Python virtual environment <intro-"
"using-virtualenv>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:206
msgid ""
"This method is a workaround for the above macOS issue, but it's an overall "
"good practice for managing dependencies and can complement the first method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:209
msgid "After any of these workarounds you should be able to install Scrapy::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:215
msgid "PyPy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:217
msgid ""
"We recommend using the latest PyPy version. For PyPy3, only Linux "
"installation was tested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:220
msgid ""
"Most Scrapy dependencies now have binary wheels for CPython, but not for "
"PyPy. This means that these dependencies will be built during installation. "
"On macOS, you are likely to face an issue with building the Cryptography "
"dependency. The solution to this problem is described `here <https://github."
"com/pyca/cryptography/issues/2692#issuecomment-272773481>`_, that is to "
"``brew install openssl`` and then export the flags that this command "
"recommends (only needed when installing Scrapy). Installing on Linux has no "
"special issues besides installing build dependencies. Installing Scrapy with "
"PyPy on Windows is not tested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:230
msgid ""
"You can check that Scrapy is installed correctly by running ``scrapy "
"bench``. If this command gives errors such as ``TypeError: ... got 2 "
"unexpected keyword arguments``, this means that setuptools was unable to "
"pick up one PyPy-specific dependency. To fix this issue, run ``pip install "
"'PyPyDispatcher>=2.1.0'``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:240
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:243
msgid "AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'OP_NO_TLSv1_1'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:245
msgid ""
"After you install or upgrade Scrapy, Twisted or pyOpenSSL, you may get an "
"exception with the following traceback::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:248
msgid ""
"[…]\n"
"  File \"[…]/site-packages/twisted/protocols/tls.py\", line 63, in <module>\n"
"    from twisted.internet._sslverify import _setAcceptableProtocols\n"
"  File \"[…]/site-packages/twisted/internet/_sslverify.py\", line 38, in "
"<module>\n"
"    TLSVersion.TLSv1_1: SSL.OP_NO_TLSv1_1,\n"
"AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'OP_NO_TLSv1_1'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:255
msgid ""
"The reason you get this exception is that your system or virtual environment "
"has a version of pyOpenSSL that your version of Twisted does not support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:258
msgid ""
"To install a version of pyOpenSSL that your version of Twisted supports, "
"reinstall Twisted with the :code:`tls` extra option::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:261
msgid "pip install twisted[tls]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/install.rst:263
msgid ""
"For details, see `Issue #2473 <https://github.com/scrapy/scrapy/"
"issues/2473>`_."
msgstr ""
